''Mark 8:34-38''

!! Introduction
Recounting an experience that we went through. Harvest Cruscades with Jack Harvey. It was a big deal to be part of the Christian club back in Pastor Patrick's day.

You would think that as the movement was gaining, this movement was the way to go! But yet Jesus started to say some weird things. Unless you eat of my flesh and drink of my blood. Unless you deny yourself and take up your cross. Slowly you start to see the crowds disperse.

As you read the drama of the New Testament. You were at the height of your popularity. You start to see the clouds not only dissipate, but at the end of the road you see the Jesus hanging on the Cross by Himself. It seems everything seems so backwards now...

We see what Jesus was doing now that everything has been done (Luke 14:26-33). Many may have thought that maybe they can follow to get free food. But here we see that Jesus says, you need to understand what it means to follow me. We need to look like passages like this to understand the gravity of what we are getting ourselves into.

It is hard nowadays to see churches that are preaching the Gospel with faithfulness. Or just out of the fear of man not wanting to offend people.

''Two Explanations of What It Means to be a Christian''

!! Being a Christian Means Following Jesus (v34)
!!! Following Jesus
"If anyone would come after me,"

The call to discipleship means to follow Him. Consider the first five books of the Bible.

Leviticus 20:23; Exodus 23:32; Numbers 15:38-40; Numbers 32:11; Deuteronomy 13:4

It is significant to say that Jesus said to follow Him. "Follow me" not just follow the Lord because Christ is worthy of being followed.

Following involves obedience. Listen to His voice and cling to me. It isn't just believing a set of facts. The demons are the ones who are confessing that Jesus is the son of God.

Being a Christian means accepting the fact that I am not the leader. It means Christ is the leader. As long as my life is about my ambition and my desires, I am not in control. God is the leader.

Where He goes, I follow. That is what it means to be a Christian.

!!! Denying Oneself
"let him deny himself"

He doesn't say there will be food when Christ is followed. His message was to follow Him and you need to deny Himself. He must increase and I must decrease. He doesn't say if we follow Him, everything will be chipper, everything will be smooth.

