!!!! Taking Up the Cross
Following Christ means taking up the Cross. In those days, Roman crucifixion was rough. 

The Cross was a shameful thing. People would walk by to see their suffering at a public humiliation. Hanged for all to see. You want people to stop killing each other, stop stealing? The Cross.

Peter had just been rebuked after getting the things right. He must do this. I came as the Messiah, I came as the Christ. Peter didn't want anything to do with that.

Galatians 2:20; 2 Corinthians 5:14-15; Matthew 10:38; Matthew 16:24; Luke 9:23

Luke 9:23 says to take up our Cross daily. You follow Me and You keep following Me. I am leading and you keep following Me. There is no following Jesus without first denying yourself and take up the Cross.

Jesus doesn't preach the message that way. He does not preach, do you want to go to Heaven or Hell? If you want to follow Me, deny yourself.

It doesn't hit us the same way. There isn't a single person on that crowd that would say they want to take up the Cross and follow Him. The message was a Gospel of foolishness as said by Paul in 1 Corinthians.

It makes not sense for multitudes to say that we are coming with you. All other roads lead to destruction. Every single minute, every single day, this life is pain and agony. At the end of it, I get glory and eternity, it is all worth it. It doesn't even compare to what is to come.

